==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Charlock
<hw>Char"lock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>cerlic</ets>; the latter part perh. fr. AS. <ets>le⟦aacute⟧c</ets>
leek. Cf. <er>Hemlock</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A cruciferous
plant (<spn>Brassica sinapistrum</spn>) with yellow flowers; wild
mustard. It is troublesome in grain fields. Called also
<altname>chardock</altname>, <altname>chardlock</altname>,
<altname>chedlock</altname>, and <altname>kedlock</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Jointed charlock</b></col>, <col><b>White
charlock</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a troublesome weed (<spn>Raphanus
Raphanistrum</spn>) with straw-colored, whitish, or purplish flowers,
and jointed pods: wild radish.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Charlotte</ent>⟦br⟧
